  "text": "In a conclusion, a factor that the most influences colonization is the type and the material of the implant. We show that PFTE (No. 3) is colonized to much less extent than Omniflow II. The number of bacteria of different species associated with various implants varies. For example in our experiment, the best colonizer is S. aureus. Aseptics and a perioperative antibiotic therapy still remain the most common methods of combating infections of vascular prostheses [CITATION_1] .",
